<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - TROUBLESHOOTING - EXTERNAL LEAKAGE AT MASTER CYLINDER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXTERNAL LEAKAGE AT MASTER CYLINDER</title>
        <table id="t0401703" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="s1t3"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CONDITION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">POSSIBLE CAUSE</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CORRECTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="2">
                            <para>External brake fluid leak, master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Leaks at outlet port brake line nuts at master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Tighten outlet port brake line nuts at master cylinder. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>. Replace
                                brake lines if required. Replace master cylinder if outlet port tube seats are damaged.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Leaks at caps on master cylinder reservoir.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Replace cap and diaphragm as required. Replace master cylinder if fill openings
                                damaged.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Leaks at any other location on the master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="s1t3">
                            <note>
                                <para>To determine if leakage is from the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster or the master
                                    cylinder, mix leaked fluid with water. Brake fluid from the master cylinder will mix
                                    with water. Power steering fluid from the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster will not mix with
                                    water.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="s1t3" align="center">
                            <note>
                                <para>A common cause of leakage at the master cylinder mounting flange is swollen seals
                                    due to putting the wrong fluid (usually power steering fluid) into the master
                                    cylinder. This is easily detectable. The diaphragms inside the fill caps of the
                                    reservoir will be swollen. If the diaphragms are swollen, the master cylinder must
                                    be replaced. Also, the calipers must be examined for swollen seals. If the caliper
                                    seals are swollen, the calipers must be repaired or replaced. Also, the brake hoses
                                    may be damaged and weakened. They should be replaced. Finally, the brake lines
                                    should be flushed with clean brake fluid until clean brake fluid comes through each
                                    of the bleeder screws at the calipers.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
